All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Athlete
Athlete class for the game project.
Club
Class representing the Club GUI.
EndScreen
EndScreen is a GUI class that represents the end screen of the game.
Game
The Game class represents the GUI for a game in the game environment.
GameEnvironment
The GameEnvironment class represents the game environment and manages various game-related functionalities.
GameResult
The GameResult class represents the GUI for displaying game results.
GameSetUp
The GameSetUp class represents the game configuration GUI window shown to the user.
GenAthlete
The GenAthlete class is responsible for generating random Athlete objects with random characteristics.
Gui
The Gui interface provides default methods for showing and closing a JFrame.
Items
The Items class represents an item that an athlete could purchase or use.
Main
The Main class serves as the entry point for the application.
MainMenu
This class represents the main menu GUI of the game.
Market
The Market class represents the market interface within the game.
Match
Match class implements the Gui interface and represents the Match screen of the game.
Player
Represents a player in the game.
TakeBye
TakeBye is a GUI class that allows the user to take a bye in the game.
Team
This class represents a team, which contains a list of athletes.
TeamSetUp
This class provides the GUI for setting up the team.
Welcome
The Welcome class represents the initial GUI window shown to the user.
